                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       South Asian Petro net up
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, May 19: South Asian Petrochem Ltd (SAPL), owned by city-based C. K. Dhanuka, has posted a 24.44 per cent increase in net profit, though its net sales declined.        
	The company, which runs a pet resin plant in Haldia, notched up a net profit of Rs 55.5 crore during the last financial year compared with Rs 44.6 crore in 2006-07.During the same period, net sales slipped to Rs 1,004.66 crore from Rs 1,018.66 crore in 2006-07.        
	The board has recommended a dividend of Rs 0.50 per equity share of Rs 10. During the period, the company increased its plant capacity from 180,000 tonnes per annum to 200,000 tonnes. The company has made a foreign exchange gain of Rs 23.20 crore in 2007-08.        
	For the fourth quarter, net sales stood at Rs 290.27 crore compared with Rs 235.74 crore in the previous corresponding quarter. Net profit was Rs 20.70 crore against Rs 17.90 crore a year ago.        
	Torrent Power         
	Torrent Power has announced a net profit of Rs 50.46 crore for the fourth quarter of 2007-08, a 13.85 per cent increase over the same period a year ago.         
	The company had a net profit of Rs 44.32 crore in the fourth quarter of 2006-07, Torrent Power said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange.                                                                                                                                     
